# Changes needing to be made to https://github.com/dcdpr/jp/pull/450
#projects/jp #task

- [x] Add `sanitize` (Done, see RFD 052)
- [ ] Remove custom `jp q help` logic, `help` is the query sent to `q` _not_ the help output, for that `--help` or `-h` should be used
- [ ] `jp init` should already work without valid config or fully loaded workspace
- [ ] That leaves `jp config show`, which _should_ require a fully loaded config _and_ a loaded workspace, because it (will) also acts on conversation configs.

Here is a fresh `jp init` + `jp query` run with the current code, showing that, even with `sanitize` hooked up, we have other things to fix to make this cold-start flow work:

```sh
$ jp init .
> Confirm before running tools? Yes (safest option)
> Select an AI model to use: anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-5
Initialized workspace at current directory

$ tree -a .
.
└── .jp
    ├── .id
    └── config.toml

1 directory, 2 files

$ jp q is this thing on?
Not found

 target  Conversation
     id  jp-c17738495321
```

